stories.text:
Received the following email today. My employer utilizes UserIQ in some of our websites and no one I've spoken to had any idea this was coming. That said, checking their website they haven't had a release since November 2019 and their blog is offline. Their website makes no mention of the shutdown.

https://www.useriq.com/

    From: user iq <useriq@useriq.com>
    Date: Wednesday, May 4, 2022 at 10:18 AM
    To: 
    Subject: UserIQ Shutdown Notice

    Please see attached notice from UserIQ.

    We regret to inform you that UserIQ (the "Company") is discontinuing
    its operations and closing its business. There are no employees or
    agents of the Company remaining to deal with any Company business or
    creditors. The Company has fully shut down and will be unable to
    further address any matters with you. The Company's application will
    continue to be available to customers for a short amount of time. All
    customer data will be deleted on May 10th. We recommend you remove the
    UserIQ tracking code from your website as soon as possible.
stories.title: UserIQ is Shutting Down May 10th

stories.text:
I’m about to graduate and it seemed obvious to aim for google or one of the other faangs until my classmate asked me, do any of them really innovate anymore?

I want to work somewhere where they are doing something new and exciting. Which companies do you think still embody this?

Some that come to mind are SpaceX, Tesla, Waymo, Meta and Microsoft are trying hard, maybe Intel
stories.title: Ask HN: Does FAANG innovate anymore? If not, where to go?

stories.text:
I have done a small experiment to see if we can predict when DALL-E 2 will generate a good image. Details about the experiment are at https://twitter.com/nutanc/status/1521906864589393920

Tl;Dr;

I think by mixing and matching we can see when Dalle 2 works.

1. Test sentence embedding on a QnA model.

2. Search Google for images on that sentence.

If both 1 and 2 work then Dalle2 will give a good result.
stories.title: Can we if predict DALL-E 2 will create a good image or not for a given text?
